  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This project is a comprehensive study, with main focus on motor control, comparing patients
      with chronic fatigue syndrome / myalgic encephalopathy (CFS/ME) and/or fibromyalgia syndrome
      (FMS). Focus of the present project will be on detailed movement analysis in a movement
      laboratory and involve functional tasks such as walking and standing. Investigations will
      also comprise muscle activity, reaction time and fine motor control.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
